#Text=Wikinews Shorts : May 20 , 2007
#Text=A compilation of brief news reports for Sunday , May 20 , 2007 .
#Text=Guantánamo detainee David Hicks back in Australia
#Text=Full report :
#Text=David Hicks transferred from Guantanamo Bay to Australian prison
#Text=A David Hicks supporter .
#Text=Image : Karen Eliot .
#Text=After five years in U.S. military custody , David Hicks has returned to Australia .
#Text=Hicks was taken to the maximum security Yatala Labour Prison , where he will serve the rest of his 9 month sentence .
#Text=His lawyer David McLeod told reporters :
#Text=" David is well and he enjoyed the trip .

column1: #Text=" ` US aid to Pak should be tied to performance on war on terror ` " — Zee News , May 20 , 2007
#Text=Olmert threatens to intensify response to rocket attacks

#Text=Prime Minister of Israel Ehud Olmert declared that : " If the measured steps we are taking , in the political and military sphere , do not bring about the desired calm , we will be forced to intensify our response . "
#Text=Olmert held Hamas and the Islamic Jihad militants responsible for the escalation in rocket attacks on Israel over the past week .
#Text=Israel answered with daily bombardments on Palestine for the past six days .
#Text=Meanwhile , the ceasefire between Hamas and Fatah seems to be holding , after a week of increased factional violence in Palestine .
